"""
Directory: src/models/

Purpose:
This directory contains model definitions used in the project. Each file provides
a function that constructs and returns a machine learning model with predefined
hyperparameters.

Note:
Although machine learning models can be directly instantiated from libraries
(e.g., scikit-learn), this project uses wrapper functions (e.g., build_random_forest,
build_naive_bayes) to standardize model creation.

This design separates model definition from experiment execution.

Rationale:
1. Reusability:
   The same model configuration can be used across multiple experiments
   (e.g., real-only, synthetic-to-real, hybrid) without rewriting code.

2. Consistency:
   All experiments use identical model settings, ensuring fair comparison
   between models and experimental setups.

3. Maintainability:
   Changes to model hyperparameters only need to be made in one place,
   instead of updating multiple scripts.

4. Clean Architecture:
   - src/models/ → defines "how to build the model"
   - src/experiments/ → defines "how the model is used"

Summary:
This directory acts as a centralized repository of model blueprints,
while training, evaluation, and dataset handling are performed in the
experiment scripts.
"""